minecraft-chunk-deleter

see:

https://code.google.com/p/minecraft-chunk-deleter/
http://www.minecraftwiki.net/wiki/Data_values
http://hydra-media.cursecdn.com/minecraft.gamepedia.com/d/d1/DataValues.svg


building:

i've included a maven POM file. just run 'mvn package' and copy the .jar out of target/


command line arguments:

--worldFolder

path to the folder containing your minecraft world

--blockIDs

a comma-seperated list of block ID values. if a blocktype in this list is found in a chunk, it will not be deleted.

--minY

the minimum height to scan for blocks (optional, default is 0)

--maxY

the maximum height to scan for blocks (optional, default is 127)

--border

the border to keep around safe chunks (optional, default is 0)

--defragment

if specified, the tool will also defragment your files (default is false)

